Class LiF

  • java.lang.Object
    • Molecule
      • Reagent
        • LiF
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Atom>

    public class LiF
extends Reagent
    LiF is a strong reagent that causes the leaving groups to leave. Then it attaches to the molecule. The leaving group (F, Cl, Br, or I) is removed from the molecule and the F- group attaches on to the molecule where the leaving group was.
    Author:
    Debbie Pao and Matthew Sit
